  "text": "Next, we describe how to decouple stochastic effects from deterministic model errors, due to local approximations. To integrate the MIEDS algorithm into ETSE, we propose to consider two triggers -one to capture local random fluctuations γ noise [CITATION_1] , and one to cope with the change in the local dynamics γ dynamics . Whenever the trigger γ noise fires, we communicate solely the current state. However, the trigger γ dynamics is responsible to detect model inaccuracies, because of entering a new region Ω i and communicate new local models when required.",
